## **8) Anything else you would like to pre-register? (e.g., secondary analyses, variables collected for exploratory purposes, unusual analyses planned?)**

The following analyses are not confirmatory but will be conducted for
exploratory purposes:

*Exploratory Factor Analysis (EFA):*

-   Run EFA on all correlate measures to examine empirical clustering

-   Compare emergent factor structure to theoretical 5-cluster framework

-   Identify potential redundancy or cross-loading items

*Confirmatory Factor Analysis (CFA):*

-   Test fit of theoretical 8-cluster model

-   Report CFI, RMSEA, SRMR fit indices

-   Compare theoretical model to EFA-derived model

*Descriptive Statistics*

-   Report % of participants above/below scale midpoints for each
    measure

-   Highlight prevalence of \"dark\" attitudes (hatred, racial
    resentment, etc.)

*Demographic Moderators*

-   Explore whether correlations differ by political orientation, race,
    gender, age

-   Not hypothesis-driven; for exploratory purposes only

*Qualitative Analysis*

-   Thematic coding of justification responses

-   Correlation between coded themes and quantitative measures

*Construct Reliability*

-   Will report Cronbach\'s alpha for all composite measures

-   Composites with Î± \< .60 will be interpreted with caution

*Multiple Comparisons*

-   Given large number of correlations, we will:

    -   Report exact p-values

    -   Apply FDR correction for construct-level analyses

    -   Focus interpretation on effect sizes rather than significance
        alone

*Open Data*

-   Full dataset will be made publicly available upon publication

-   All materials (survey, measures, analysis code) will be shared

*Deviations from Pre-Registration*

-   Any deviations will be transparently reported in the manuscript
